<MSGOh.<NOD Hey.<NOD You found me.<NOD<CLRYeah, it's me.<NOD ZarroTsu.<NOD
"Zarro Tsukei", as the alias goes.<NOD<CLRI suppose you want a reward for
finding this place?<NOD<CLRAlready taken care of.<NOD
Trust me on this one.<NOD<FL+2351<END
#0202
<MSGThere are a total of five of these
rooms in the game.<NOD
Maybe if you find all five of
them, something good will happen.<NOD
I dunno yet.<NOD It's just a hunch.<NOD<FL+2352<END
#0203
<MSGI wonder how the mod will be
received?<NOD I'll admit, I wasn't
terribly kind when I returned to
the community.<NOD Could have gone
a bit better.<NOD<CLRI was hoping to keep myself
hidden from the rest of the
community longer than I did.<NOD
Guess I'm not one for the
stealthy approach, huh?<NOD<FL+2353<END
#0204
<MSGJeez, are you done yet?<NOD The
more you talk to me, the less time
I have to work on the game.<NOD<CLRYes, I know that sounds
confusing as heck!<NOD Maybe you
should go off and save Curly
instead of messing around here!<NOD<FL+2354<END
#0205
<MSGCave Story's a pretty great game.<NOD
You should try copying your save-
data over sometime.<NOD<CLRAlthough, TRY to only load
save files from the Prefab House,
before the Sacred Ground.<NOD
You can still load the game from
elsewhere if you WANT...<NOD but don't
come crying to me if you get stuck
in a wall or the game crashes.<NOD<FL+2355<END
#0206
<MSG....................<NOD
(He'll leave any second now...)<NOD<END
#0211
<FLJ2360:0216<FLJ2359:0215<FLJ2358:0214<FLJ2357:0213<FLJ2356:0212
<MSGUsed the momentum of your jump to
get through the tunnel, did you?<NOD
Well, aren't you clever?<NOD<CLRAnyway, this is the second secret
room in the game.<NOD If you haven't
found the first, I'm really quite
surprised.<NOD The first one is a
little bit easier to get to than
this one is!<NOD<FL+2356<FLJ2252:0000<CLRIf you really did miss it,
you can still go back and find
it if you want.<NOD I won't
tell you where it is, though.<NOD<END
#0212
<MSGDepending on your save file when
you copy a profile over, you can
get all sorts of cool goodies.<NOD
I won't go into detail of what
these goodies are, but that's
the fun of it!<NOD Gotta play the
original game differently, and
reap the rewards!<NOD<FL+2357<END
#0213
<MSGSomething other than weapons
that is affected by an old profile
copy is life capsules.<NOD
If, for example, you didn't
collect any life capsules in your
original run of the game,<NOD
you'll be able to recollect them
all while playing this one.<NOD<FL+2358<END
#0214
<MSGThat said, if you did collect
them in the original game, you'll
immediately be able to tell.<NOD
You'll start out with twice as
much health, making the beginning
of the game much easier.<NOD<CLROf course, in order to get the
highest possible health count,
you'll have to miss them all!<NOD<FL+2359<END
#0215
<MSGWhile writing the past two
messages, I was debating on saying
missiles act the same way.<NOD
However, if that were true, the
difference in numbers would be far
less effective between the two.<NOD<CLRBesides, who ever heard of
a player refusing to collect all
the missiles in the original game?<NOD
That's highly unlikely!<NOD<FL+2360<END
#0216
<MSGThere.<NOD I'm all out of
things to exposit.<NOD<CLR
Are you happy now?<NOD<END
#0221
<FLJ2365:0226<FLJ2364:0225<FLJ2363:0224<FLJ2362:0223<FLJ2361:0222
<MSGOh, hello (again?).<NOD
I was worried nobody would
think to look here for this
secret room, ha-ha.<NOD<CLROr, wait, are you really,
REALLY lost in the teleporter
puzzle?<NOD That would make this
kind of awkward.<NOD<FL+2361<END
#0222
<MSGMissiles took an interesting
turn in this mod, as the Super
Missiles are even more optional.<NOD
If you're lucky, you should run
into someone who will upgrade
them for you in the Labyrinth.<NOD<FL+2362<END
#0223
<MSGIf you've been playing from an
original game file, keep an eye
out for capsule-openers, shortly.<NOD
There will be a few instances 
where you'll have to speak with
them more than once at a time.<NOD<FL+2363<END
#0224
<MSGLater on you're gonna fight an
interesting boss combination, on
an interesting map.<NOD
I had to actually teleport the
player to a seperate map for it
to work properly!<NOD<CLRI mean, I suppose I could have
done it normally, but who am I to
give up a fadeless teleport?<NOD<FL+2364<END
#0225
<MSGIn the original mod of the game,
riding Monster X was supposed to
be mandatory.<NOD I've since changed
this to be way, way more
optional than before.<NOD I imagine
when people find that out,
they'll hate me for it.<NOD<CLRThat said, if you were trying to
speed-run the game, you'd really
have no choice but to ride him!<NOD<FL+2365<END
#0226
<MSGGack, my throat is sore now.<NOD
Do you think you can get me a
glass of water while you're out?<NOD<END
#0231
<FLJ2370:0236<FLJ2369:0235<FLJ2368:0234<FLJ2367:0233<FLJ2366:0232
<MSGOh!<NOD Oh, shoot, you trapped
yourself in the corner of Sand
Zone, didn't you?<NOD<CLR
Hold on a sec!<NOD<CLR
..........<NOD<CLROkay, there!<NOD That teleporter goes
to the Labyrinth now!<NOD<CLR
...What?<NOD<FL+2366<END
#0232
<MSGDevoting your free time to a
single project is rather emotion-
consuming.<NOD I don't regret it,
and I certainly won't abandon it,
but it leaves me feeling empty.<NOD
Like there are other things I
could do instead, but then...<NOD
Those things would be distracting
from time that could be spent on
the mod, instead.<NOD<CLR
Does that make me sound fickle?<NOD<FL+2367<END
#0233
<MSGDid you know there's an exp-
capsule hidden in this room?<NOD
The ceiling over to the left is
fake.<NOD<CLRI would've mentioned it earlier,
but...<NOD Well, that would make
things a little unfair.<NOD<FL+2368<END
#0234
<MSGAlright, lemme think.<NOD
What haven't I indulged you in?<NOD
Well, there are two additional
items from the original game that
will 'transfer over' in a way.<NOD<CLRThe first is the Little Man.<NOD
You might even have him in your
pocket right now for all I know.<NOD
Give him a chat every once in a
while if you like.<NOD<CLRThe other is the Ikachan medal.<NOD
There's no such medal in this
mod, but it WILL let you start
the game with the =Map System=.<NOD<FL+2369<END
#0235
<MSGI've also been messing around
with the weapons a lot lately,
trying to balance them.<NOD
The =Snake= had a major revamp
in how it deals damage so that
it isn't too overpowered.<NOD
Since it pierces through enemies
en masse, it makes the first boss
a lot easier to deal with.<NOD<FL+2370<END
#0236
<MSGAnd that's...<NOD
All I really have to talk about.<NOD<END
