#0301
<MSG
February 2nd, 2013; 12:53 AM.<NOD<CLRSlowly but surely I work on the
first caves.<NOD I think I've taken
on an obsession in doing so.<NOD
I can't seem to quite pull myself
from polishing this stuff before
I move on.<NOD<CLR
A friend of mine has agreed to do
new graphics for some of the
largest bosses in the game-to-be.<NOD<CLRHis life has been kind of hectic
lately, though.<NOD I'm not sure
if he'll really have the time
to do it...<NOD<END
#0302
<MSG
February 17th, 2013; 3:02 PM.<NOD<CLRIt's time to put out the first
demo of this mod remake.<NOD
A "re-mod", if you will.<NOD<CLRI've put a lot of work
into it, and hopefully people
appreciate that.<NOD I dare
say I put more work into it
than Shmitz originally intended!<NOD<CLROf course, it was never my
intent to upstage him.<NOD
I always loved the original game,
in concept...<NOD But its incompletion
leaves a bit of a hole in my
heart.<NOD Especially after a good
five years since its conception...<NOD<CLRI hope wherever he ran off
to, he'll one day look back at
what I have done in his stead.<NOD
That way, he can feel great
pride in knowing how much of
an impact his mod really holds.<NOD<END
#0303
<MSG
May 8th, 2013; 7:36 PM.<NOD<CLRThe Labyrinth is done.<NOD
Took a few weeks, in fact, and
entirely due to my schedule.<NOD
It can't be helped.<NOD<CLRI'd like to say there's only a
"few" more things to do before
the second demo, but...<NOD
Well, I'm still debating on
having both Genesis AND
Oblivion available.<NOD<CLRUltimately, though, there's a lot
of other minor bases I need to
cover first.<NOD The =Nemesis= is
almost immediately available
after the Labyrinth, and there's
loads of other little things
that I need to write out, too.<NOD<CLRI wonder if the second demo
will contain a second secret
room as well.<NOD<END
#0304
<MSG
June 29th, 2013; 2:32 PM.<NOD<CLRIt has been over four months
since I released the first demo.<NOD
I am nearing the completion of
the second demo too, now, and am
looking to release it very soon.<NOD<CLRThe portions of the game that are
in this demo were very mechanic-
intensive, and took a long time.<NOD
I intended to add even more to
this demo, but...<NOD Well, I feel
that everyone's been waiting more
than long enough.<NOD<CLRI just hope I'm doing things
right, and not just stumbling
through the dark like a moron.<NOD
This stuff is time-consuming,
and I'd hate for it to all have
been a massive waste of time.<NOD<END
#0305
<MSG
April 19th, 2014; 10:35 PM.<NOD<CLRI haven't written a diary for
a secret room in a long time.<NOD
Has it really been 10 months...?<NOD<CLRThe game is almost complete, and
I hope I can get it out by the
end of the month.<NOD It's cutting
it close, but...<NOD<CLRAt the time of writing, I've only
a few pieces of dialog left to
write near the end of the game.<NOD
That and some ASM for the final
boss, which might take the
longest...<NOD<CLROn the other hand, a lot of
the time spent on this mod has
been procrastinating the dialog,<NOD
so for all I know that might
take equally as long...<NOD<END
